name: Kopi Bali Mutiara - Pupuan
address: Jl. Raya Pupuan, Batungsel, Tabanan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82163, Indonesia
review 1: Taste soooo good love the aroma of the  coffee , well doneüëã
review 2:
Kopi Mutiara is a family owned company.
The founder is still alive and is over 100 years old üëç
The point of difference is in the way that they roast the coffee..
It's done traditionally in hand rotated drums that are roasted over a wood fire üëç
This part of the process gives their coffee a unique smoky flavour..
Earthy and strong I've never tasted anything else like this üëç
I understand that the Batungsel village and the villages on either side are the main customers.
They also export to South Korea..

Well worth the trip for some exceptional coffee.
They have both Arabica and Robusta coffee varieties
Would I buy again ü§î
Most definitely üëçüëçüëç
review 3: Lovely place, though near road. Staff are very friendly. The coffee is ground and packaged in the locale. Coffee from this place is local and smoother than the common one from ABC. Hardly any bitterness! Will recommend further.
review 4: I often stop here on my way home just to get or buy coffee powder. This is just the best coffee product produced locally. Coffee with the best tase.
review 5: Very good local coffee for an excellent price.
